clinical_study.brief_title: Observational Registry Study: FIREHAWK DES for Treating Coronary Artery Disease (CAD)
clinical_study.official_title: A Prospective Multicenter Single-Arm Observational Registry Study Assessing the Safety and Efficacy of FIREHAWK Biodegradable Polymer Target-release Rapamycin-eluting Stent for the Treatment of Coronary Artery Disease: TARGET II

brief_summary.textblock: The study aims to further assess the safety, efficacy and the performance of its delivery system of FIREHAWK rapamycin-eluting stent up to five years.

detailed_description.textblock: This is a prospective open-labeled, multi-center, single-arm observational registry study. Approximately 1,100 subjects will be enrolled to evaluate the TLF as the primary endpoint at 12-month. Also, the study will follow up those subjects up to 5 years as the secondary endpoints.

arm_group.description: Using Firehawk biodegradable polymer rapamycin-eluting stent for CAD

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Age 18-75, male or unpregnant women
- Evidence of non-symptomatic ischemia, stable or non-stable angina or past MI
- Native coronary artery target lesion
- Target lesion length <=60mm, target lesion vessel diameter 2.25mm-4.0mm
- Target lesion diameter stenosis>=70%
- For each target lesion, Firehawk stent implantation only
- Understand the study purpose, willing to participate and sign the letter of consent
- Acceptance of clinical follow-up
Exclusion Criteria:
- Acute MI within 72 hours
- Unprotected LM and intervention-required three-vessel lesions
- Calcified lesion failed in pre-dilation and twisted lesion
- Bridge vessel lesion
- Any stent implanted within one year
- Severe heart failure (HYHA>=III) or LVEF<40%
- Renal deficiency, blood creatinine > 2.0mg/dl
- Bleeding tendency
- Allergic to aspirin, clopidogrel, ticlopidine, dye, rapamycin and metal
- Life expectation <12 months
- History of not achieving study finish
- No compliances to the protocol
- Heart implantation subjects
